fields.description: Gets or sets the Active Directory site.
fields.name: ActiveDirectorySiteCode

fields.description: Enables or disables whether the Kerberos extension can automatically determine its site name.
fields.name: BlockActiveDirectorySiteAutoDiscovery

fields.description: Enables or disables Keychain usage.
fields.name: BlockAutomaticLogin

fields.description: Gets or sets the Generic Security Services name of the Kerberos cache to use for this profile.
fields.name: CacheName

fields.description: Gets or sets a list of app Bundle IDs allowed to access the Kerberos Ticket Granting Ticket.
fields.name: CredentialBundleIdAccessControlList

fields.description: When set to True, the credential is requested on the next matching Kerberos challenge or network state change. When the credential is expired or missing, a new credential is created. Available for devices running macOS versions 12 and later.
fields.name: CredentialsCacheMonitored

fields.description: Gets or sets a list of realms for custom domain-realm mapping. Realms are case sensitive.
fields.name: DomainRealms

fields.description: Gets or sets a list of hosts or domain names for which the app extension performs SSO.
fields.name: Domains

fields.description: When true, this profile's realm will be selected as the default. Necessary if multiple Kerberos-type profiles are configured.
fields.name: IsDefaultRealm

fields.description: When set to True, the Kerberos extension allows any apps entered with the app bundle ID, managed apps, and standard Kerberos utilities, such as TicketViewer and klist, to access and use the credential. Available for devices running macOS versions 12 and later.
fields.name: KerberosAppsInBundleIdACLIncluded

fields.description: When set to True, the Kerberos extension allows managed apps, and any apps entered with the app bundle ID to access the credential. When set to False, the Kerberos extension allows all apps to access the credential. Available for devices running iOS and iPadOS versions 14 and later.
fields.name: ManagedAppsInBundleIdACLIncluded

fields.description: Select how other processes use the Kerberos Extension credential.
fields.name: ModeCredentialUsed

fields.description: Enables or disables password changes.
fields.name: PasswordBlockModification

fields.description: Gets or sets the URL that the user will be sent to when they initiate a password change.
fields.name: PasswordChangeUrl

fields.description: Enables or disables password syncing. This won't affect users logged in with a mobile account on macOS.
fields.name: PasswordEnableLocalSync

fields.description: Overrides the default password expiration in days. For most domains, this value is calculated automatically.
fields.name: PasswordExpirationDays

fields.description: Gets or sets the number of days until the user is notified that their password will expire (default is 15).
fields.name: PasswordExpirationNotificationDays

fields.description: Gets or sets the minimum number of days until a user can change their password again.
fields.name: PasswordMinimumAgeDays

fields.description: Gets or sets the minimum length of a password.
fields.name: PasswordMinimumLength

fields.description: Gets or sets the number of previous passwords to block.
fields.name: PasswordPreviousPasswordBlockCount

fields.description: Enables or disables whether passwords must meet Active Directory's complexity requirements.
fields.name: PasswordRequireActiveDirectoryComplexity

fields.description: Gets or sets a description of the password complexity requirements.
fields.name: PasswordRequirementsDescription

fields.description: Add creates an ordered list of preferred Key Distribution Centers (KDCs) to use for Kerberos traffic. This list is used when the servers are not discoverable using DNS. When the servers are discoverable, the list is used for both connectivity checks, and used first for Kerberos traffic. If the servers don’t respond, then the device uses DNS discovery. Delete removes an existing list, and devices use DNS discovery. Available for devices running macOS versions 12 and later.
fields.name: PreferredKDCs

fields.description: Gets or sets the case-sensitive realm name for this profile.
fields.name: Realm

fields.description: Gets or sets whether to require authentication via Touch ID, Face ID, or a passcode to access the keychain entry.
fields.name: RequireUserPresence

fields.description: Text displayed to the user at the Kerberos sign in window. Available for devices running iOS and iPadOS versions 14 and later.
fields.name: SignInHelpText

fields.description: When set to True, LDAP connections are required to use Transport Layer Security (TLS). Available for devices running macOS versions 11 and later.
fields.name: TlsForLDAPRequired

fields.description: Gets or sets the principle user name to use for this profile. The realm name does not need to be included.
fields.name: UserPrincipalName

fields.description: When set to True, the user isn’t prompted to set up the Kerberos extension until the extension is enabled by the admin, or a Kerberos challenge is received. Available for devices running macOS versions 11 and later.
fields.name: UserSetupDelayed

fields.description: This label replaces the user name shown in the Kerberos extension. You can enter a name to match the name of your company or organization. Available for devices running macOS versions 11 and later.
fields.name: UsernameLabelCustom
